CatDescriptText: Cutline of reverse image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 31, 1956, page A1, reads: "Distance No Problem - Some of the 800 guests, who attended the Human Rights Dinner at the Gateway Plaza, traveled some distance in order to join with fellow NAACP sympathizers. Among those, coming from "afar," were, left to right: Mark H. Ellicott, president, Connellsville NAACP; Miss Corinne Garside, New Castle NAACP Branch; Larry R. Jackson, president Cardale Branch; Harry K. McCraw, president Monessen Branch; Frank D. Davis, president, Johnstown Branch, and Thomas J. Berrett, Johnstown, Pa. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Mark H. Ellicott, Corinne Garside, Larry R. Jackson, Harry K. McCraw, Frank D. Davis, and Thomas J. Berrett, seated at banquet table number "55" for Human Rights Dinner at Gateway Plaza, Downtown
